args.canonical_rel_desc: The subject is a broader set or category of ethical dilemmas in AI development that includes the object as a specific ethical issue or example.
args.justification: In both relations, 'ethical dilemmas in AI development' is the broader concept and the object (surveillance purposes, biased data) is a specific ethical issue that is part of that set; this is a category-membership relation from category to member.

args.canonical_rel_desc: The subject is a specific ethical issue or concern that is part of, or discussed within, the broader set or category of ethical dilemmas in AI development (the object).
args.justification: In these three relations, the subject (job displacement, inequality, concentration of power) is a concrete ethical concern that belongs to the broader concept 'ethical dilemmas in AI development' (object), expressing membership from member to category.

All five relations link specific ethical issues (surveillance, biased data, job displacement, inequality, concentration of power) with the broader concept 'ethical dilemmas in AI development' via a membership/part-of-a-set semantics; they are variants of the same family of ethical issue membership relations, differing only in direction.

These relations express conceptual membership/association between a general category of ethical dilemmas and particular issues, not composition, causality, or spatial/temporal relations; they best fit a broad association/grouping dimension.
